SIMPLE: confinement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Confinement
<hw>Con*fine"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Restraint within limits; imprisonment; any restraint of liberty;
seclusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mind hates restraint, and is apt to fancy itself under
<qex>confinement</qex> when the sight is pent up.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Restraint within doors by sickness, esp. that caused
by childbirth; lying-in.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confiner</ent>⟦br⟧
